aining loss:      {trainer_stats.metrics['train_loss']:.4f}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Step 8: Save the LoRA Adapter\n\nThe trained LoRA adapter weights and the tokenizer are saved to disk. Only the adapter weights are saved, not the full base model, keeping the output size manageable. Adapter size and remaining disk space are reported after saving.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH = \"/kaggle/working/nemotron_lora_adapter\"\n# model.save_pretrained(ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH, safe_serialization=True)\n# tokenizer.save_pretrained(ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH)\n\n# # Report disk usage\n# import shutil\n# adapter_size = sum(\n#     os.path.getsize(os.path.join(dp, f))\n#     for dp, _, fns in os.walk(ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH)\n#     for f in fns\n# ) / (1024 * 1024)\n# disk_usage = shutil.disk_usage(\"/kaggle/working\")\n# print(f\"\\n LoRA adapter saved to: {ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH}\")\n# print(f\"   Adapter size: {adapter_size:.1f} MB\")\n# print(f\"   Disk remaining: {disk_usage.free / (1024**3):.1f} GB\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Step 9: Inference Test\n\nA quick inference test is run to verify the model has learned the required output format. A math problem is passed to the model with the reasoning system prompt active. The generated output is checked for:\n\n- A closing `</think>` tag -- confirms the model learned to close its chain-of-thought block.\n- A `\\\\boxed{}` final answer -- confirms the model learned to produce a structured answer.\n\nIf both are present, Phase 1 is considered successful.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# print(\"\\n RUNNING INFERENCE TEST...\\n\")\n\n# model.eval()\n\n# # Build prompt directly — model generates everything after <think>\n# test_prompt = (\n#     \"<|im_start|>system\\n\"\n#     \"detailed thinking on<|im_end|>\\n\"\n#     \"<|im_start|>user\\n\"\n#     \"If f(x) = x^2 + 3x - 4, find all values of x where f(x) = 0. Show full working.<|im_end|>\\n\"\n#     \"<|im_start|>assistant\\n\"\n#     \"<think>\\n\"\n# )\n\n# inputs = tokenizer(test_prompt, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(\"cuda\")\n# prompt_len = inputs[\"input_ids\"].shape[1]\n\n# with torch.inference_mode():\n#     outputs = model.generate(\n#         **inputs,\n#         max_new_tokens  = 1024,\n#         temperature     = 0.6,\n#         top_p           = 0.95,\n#         do_sample       = True,\n#         eos_token_id    = tokenizer.eos_token_id,\n#         repetition_penalty = 1.1\n#     )\n\n# # Decode full output and generated-only portion separately\n# full_response = tokenizer.decode(outputs[0], skip_special_tokens=False)\n# generated_text = tokenizer.decode(outputs[0][prompt_len:], skip_special_tokens=False)\n\n# print(\"--- FULL OUTPUT ---\")\n# print(full_response)\n# print(\"-------------------\")\n# print(\"\\n--- GENERATED PORTION ONLY ---\")\n# print(generated_text)\n# print(\"-------------------\")\n\n# # Validate format on generated text only (not the injected prompt)\n# has_think_close = \"</think>\" in generated_text\n# has_boxed = \"\\\\boxed{\" in generated_text\n\n# if has_think_close and has_boxed:\n#     print(\"\\n PHASE 1 MISSION SUCCESS — <think>...</think> + \\\\boxed{} confirmed.\")\n# elif has_think_close:\n#     print(\"\\n  </think> found but \\\\boxed{} missing in output.\")\n# elif has_boxed:\n#     print(\"\\n  \\\\boxed{} found but </think> closure missing — format partially learned.\")\n# else:\n#     print(\"\\n WARNING — Neither </think> nor \\\\boxed{} detected. More training may be needed.\")\n\n# # Final cleanup\n# del inputs, outputs\n# gc.collect()\n# torch.cuda.empty_cache()\n\n# print(\"PHASE 1 COMPLETE (supervised Fine tuning for Nemotron completed).\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Section 2: Phase 2 — BAPO (Balanced Policy Optimization with Adaptive Clipping)\n\nStandard GRPO has four structural flaws when training reasoning models on hard mathematical datasets:\n1. **Symmetric Clipping:** Caps the learning signal on rare, hard-won correct answers.\n2. **All-Miss Groups:** Generates zero gradients but still wastes massive backward-pass compute.\n3. **Sequence-Level Loss:** Disincentivizes long, complex reasoning chains.\n4. **The Verbosity Trap:** Token-level loss can cause the model to artificially bloat its output to farm gradients.\n\n**The Solution:** I am implementing **BAPO** (Balanced Policy Optimization with Adaptive Clipping). We introduce asymmetric clipping (eps_low=0.2, eps_high=0.5) to maximize learning on breakthroughs, sampling to skip dead batches, token-level loss weighting, and a length-penalized reward function to enforce efficient logic.\n\n**NOTE:** I am implemented DAPO first but with more research Found out BAPO to be the optimal solution\n\n**INSPIRATION:-**\nCode from TRL's github: https://github.com/huggingface/trl\nCode from BAPO's github: https://github.com/WooooDyy/BAPO\n\n**CITATIONS**\n\n\n@software{vonwerra2020trl,\n  title   = {{TRL: Transformers Reinforcement Learning}},\n  author  = {von Werra, Leandro and Belkada, Younes and Tunstall, Lewis and Beeching, Edward and Thrush, Tristan and Lambert, Nathan and Huang, Shengyi and Rasul, Kashif and Gallouédec, Quentin},\n  license = {Apache-2.0},\n  url     = {https://github.com/huggingface/trl},\n  year    = {2020}\n}\n\n\n\n@misc{xi2025bapostabilizingoffpolicyreinforcement,\n      title={BAPO: Stabilizing Off-Policy Reinforcement Learning for LLMs via Balanced Policy Optimization with Adaptive Clipping}, \n      author={Zhiheng Xi and Xin Guo and Yang Nan and Enyu Zhou and Junrui Shen and Wenxiang Chen and Jiaqi Liu and Jixuan Huang and Zhihao Zhang and Honglin Guo and Xun Deng and Zhikai Lei and Miao Zheng and Guoteng Wang and Shuo Zhang and Peng Sun and Rui Zheng and Hang Yan and Tao Gui and Qi Zhang and Xuanjing Huang},\n      year={2025},\n      eprint={2510.18927},\n      archivePrefix={arXiv},\n      primaryClass={cs.LG},\n      url={https://arxiv.org/abs/2510.18927}, \n}\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Step 1: Reload the SFT Adapter and Load the GRPO Dataset\n\nThe base model is already in memory from Section 1. We reload the SFT adapter so GRPO\nstarts from the fine-tuned checkpoint — not from the raw base model.\n\nThe GRPO dataset (`FINAL_DATA_GRPO.csv`) must contain **`question`** and **`answer`** columns.\nThe `answer` column must include a `\\\\boxed{}` ground-truth so the correctness reward can fire.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import gc\nimport torch\nimport os\nimport re\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom datasets import load_dataset, Dataset\nfrom peft import PeftModel, LoraConfig, get_peft_model\nfrom transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer\nimport datasets\nimport collections\n\ndatasets.utils.logging.disable_progress_bar()\n\nBASE_MODEL_PATH = \"/kaggle/input/models/metric/nemotron-3-nano-30b-a3b-bf16/transformers/default/1\"\nADAPTER_3_PATH = \"/kaggle/input/datasets/banwait13/lora-adapter/NEMOTRON\"\n\nif 'model' not in globals() or model is None:\n    print(\"[DAPO] Loading Base Model...\")\n    model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n        BASE_MODEL_PATH,\n        device_map=\"auto\",\n        torch_dtype=torch.bfloat16,\n        trust_remote_code=True,\n    )\n    tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(BASE_MODEL_PATH, trust_remote_code=True)\n    if tokenizer.unk_token is not None:\n        tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.unk_token\n    else:\n        tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n    tokenizer.padding_side = \"right\"\n\n    print(\"[DAPO] Attaching Adapter 3 as trainable...\")\n    model = PeftModel.from_pretrained(model, ADAPTER_3_PATH, is_trainable=True)\n    print(f\"[DAPO] Adapter loaded. Trainable params: {sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters() if p.requires_grad):,}\")\nelse:\n    print(\"[DAPO] Model already in memory.\")\n\n# ── NUCLEAR FIX: Manually apply gradient checkpointing ────────────────────\n# NemotronHForCausalLM does not declare gradient checkpointing support,\n# so gradient_checkpointing_enable() throws a ValueError.\n# We bypass the method entirely and do what it does internally.\nimport functools as _ft\nfrom torch.utils.checkpoint import checkpoint as _torch_ckpt\n\nmodel.config.use_cache = False\n_gc_fn = _ft.partial(_torch_ckpt, use_reentrant=False)\nfor _m in model.modules():\n    if hasattr(_m, 'gradient_checkpointing'):\n        _m.gradient_checkpointing = True\n    _m._gradient_checkpointing_func = _gc_fn\n\nif hasattr(model, \"enable_input_require_grads\"):\n    model.enable_input_require_grads()\n\nprint(\"[DAPO] Gradient checkpointing force-applied (manual bypass).\")\n\n# ── Load FULL dataset (1000 samples) ─────────────────────────────────────────\n_raw_dataset = load_dataset(\n    \"csv\",\n    data_files=\"/kaggle/input/datasets/banwait13/lora-adapter/DATASETS/GRPO_TEST.csv\",\n    split=\"train\",\n)\n\ndef normalize_cols(sample):\n    question = (\n        sample.get(\"instruction\") or sample.get(\"prompt\")\n        or sample.get(\"question\") or \"\"\n    )\n    answer = (\n        sample.get(\"response\") or sample.get(\"answer\")\n        or sample.get(\"output\") or \"\"\n    )\n    return {\n        \"question\":    str(question).strip(),\n        \"answer\":      str(answer).strip(),\n    }\n\n_raw_dataset = _raw_dataset.map(normalize_cols, num_proc=2)\n\n# ── Auto-categorize puzzles from instruction text ─────────────────────────────\ndef _categorize_instruction(text: str) -> str:\n    t = str(text).lower()\n    if \"gravitational\" in t or \"falling distance\" in t or \"d = 0.5*g*t\" in t:\n        return \"gravity\"\n    elif \"bit manipulation\" in t or \"binary\" in t:\n        return \"bit_manipulation\"\n    elif \"decrypt\" in t or \"encrypt\" in t or \"cipher\" in t:\n        return \"encryption\"\n    elif \"unit conversion\" in t or \"convert the following measurement\" in t:\n        return \"unit_conversion\"\n    elif \"numeral\" in t or \"roman\" in t:\n        return \"roman_numeral\"\n    elif \"transformation rules\" in t or \"transformation\" in t:\n        return \"transformation\"\n    else:\n        return \"other\"\n\n_raw_dataset = _raw_dataset.map(\n    lambda x: {\"puzzle_type\": _categorize_instruction(x[\"question\"])},\n    desc=\"Categorizing puzzles\",\n)\n\n# ── Build prompts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndef build_grpo_prompt(example: dict) -> str:\n    question_with_hint = (\n        example[\"question\"]\n        + \"\\nPlease put your final answer inside `\\\\boxed{}`. \" \n        + \"For example: `\\\\boxed{your answer}`\"\n        + \"You are an elite mathematical and cryptographic reasoning assistant. \"\n        +  \"You MUST think step-by-step. \"\n        + \"First, write out your entire thought process inside <think> and </think> tags. \"\n    )\n    try:\n        prompt = tokenizer.apply_chat_template(\n            [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": question_with_hint}],\n            tokenize=False,\n            add_generation_prompt=True,\n            enable_thinking=True,\n        )\n    except Exception:\n        prompt = (\n            \"<|im_start|>system\\ndetailed thinking on<|im_end|>\\n\"\n            f\"<|im_start|>user\\n{question_with_hint}<|im_end|>\\n\"\n            \"<|im_start|>assistant\\n\"\n        )\n    return prompt\n\n_raw_dataset = _raw_dataset.map(\n    lambda x: {\"prompt\": build_grpo_prompt(x)},\n    desc=\"Building DAPO prompts\",\n)\n\n# ── Per-category dataset splits for sequential DAPO runs ──────────────────────\n# Strategy: 3 sequential runs on the SAME adapter, each specializing in\n# a cluster of related problem types. This prevents the model from having\n# to context-switch between completely unrelated reasoning strategies.\n#\n# Run ordering: easiest → hardest (so the adapter warms up on solvable problems)\n\nBAPO_RUNS = [\n    {\n        \"name\": \"numerical\",\n        \"cats\": [\"gravity\", \"unit_conversion\"],\n        \"description\": \"Physics + unit conversion (numerical reasoning)\",\n        \"lr\": 5e-6,\n        \"max_steps\": 80,\n    },\n    {\n        \"name\": \"cipher\",\n        \"cats\": [\"transformation\", \"encryption\"],\n        \"description\": \"Pattern transforms + cipher decryption\",\n        \"lr\": 3e-6,\n        \"max_steps\": 80,\n    },\n    {\n        \"name\": \"symbolic\",\n        \"cats\": [\"bit_manipulation\", \"roman_numeral\", \"other\"],\n        \"description\": \"Bit ops + roman numerals + misc\",\n        \"lr\": 3e-6,\n        \"max_steps\": 50,\n    },\n]\n\n# Build category subsets (shuffle within each, but keep category grouping)\nbapo_run_datasets = {}\nfor run_cfg in BAPO_RUNS:\n    subset = _raw_dataset.filter(\n        lambda x, cats=run_cfg[\"cats\"]: x[\"puzzle_type\"] in cats,\n        desc=f\"Filtering {run_cfg['name']}\",\n    )\n    # Shuffle within the subset\n    subset = subset.shuffle(seed=3407)\n    bapo_run_datasets[run_cfg[\"name\"]] = subset\n\n# Clean up columns: keep only what BAPOTrainer needs\nkeep = {\"question\", \"answer\", \"puzzle_type\", \"prompt\"}\nfor name in bapo_run_datasets:\n    ds = bapo_run_datasets[name]\n    drop = [c for c in ds.column_names if c not in keep]\n    if drop:\n        bapo_run_datasets[name] = ds.remove_columns(drop)\n\n# Also keep a combined dataset as fallback\ngrpo_dataset = _raw_dataset.shuffle(seed=3407)\ndrop = [c for c in grpo_dataset.column_names if c not in keep]\nif drop:\n    grpo_dataset = grpo_dataset.remove_columns(drop)\n\n# ── Report ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nprint(f\"\\n[DAPO] Full dataset: {len(_raw_dataset):,} samples\")\ncounts = collections.Counter(_raw_dataset[\"puzzle_type\"])\nfor k, v in sorted(counts.items()):\n    print(f\"  {k:20s}: {v:4d}  ({100*v/len(_raw_dataset):.1f}%)\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n[DAPO] Sequential run plan ({len(BAPO_RUNS)} runs):\")\nfor run_cfg in BAPO_RUNS:\n    ds = bapo_run_datasets[run_cfg[\"name\"]]\n    print(f\"  Run '{run_cfg['name']}': {len(ds):4d} samples | LR={run_cfg['lr']:.0e} | steps={run_cfg['max_steps']} | {run_cfg['description']}\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n[DAPO] Total training steps: {sum(r['max_steps'] for r in BAPO_RUNS)}\")\ngc.collect()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-11T19:41:14.356927Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-11T19:41:14.357097Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-11T19:41:47.487204Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-11T19:41:14.357085Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-11T19:41:47.486917Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"[DAPO] Model already in memory.\n[DAPO] Gradient checkpointing force-applied (manual bypass).\n\n[DAPO] Full dataset: 262 samples\n  bit_manipulation    :   34  (13.0%)\n  encryption          :   30  (11.5%)\n  gravity             :   86  (32.8%)\n  roman_numeral       :   12  (4.6%)\n  transformation      :   69  (26.3%)\n  unit_conversion     :   31  (11.8%)\n\n[DAPO] Sequential run plan (3 runs):\n  Run 'numerical':  117 samples | LR=5e-06 | steps=80 | Physics + unit conversion (numerical reasoning)\n  Run 'cipher':   99 samples | LR=3e-06 | steps=80 | Pattern transforms + cipher decryption\n  Run 'symbolic':   46 samples | LR=3e-06 | steps=50 | Bit ops + roman numerals + misc\n\n[DAPO] Total training steps: 210\n","output_type":"stream"},{"execution_count":17,"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":"71399"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":17},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Step 2: Define the BAPO Reward Functions\n\nGRPO scores completions automatically using **reward functions**. We add a new **Verbosity Penalty** here (Flaw 4 Fix) to ensure the model finds the most mathematically efficient reasoning path rather than just rambling to farm gradients.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import re\nimport math\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# 5-REWARD SYSTEM\n# Ceiling: reward_format(1.0) + reward_thinking_quality(0.5)\n#        + reward_correctness(2.0) + reward_numerical(1.5)\n#        + reward_no_hacking(0.5)  =  5.5 pts total\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nBOXED_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"\\\\boxed\\{([^{}]*(?:\\{[^{}]*\\}[^{}]*)*)\\}\")\n\ndef _get_text(comp):\n    return comp[0][\"content\"] if isinstance(comp, list) else comp\n\ndef extract_boxed(text: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return the LAST \\\\boxed{} — avoids intermediate reasoning boxes.\"\"\"\n    matches = BOXED_PATTERN.findall(text)\n    return matches[-1].strip() if matches else \"\"\n\ndef _norm(s: str) -> str:\n    return re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \"\", s.strip()).lower()\n\ndef _try_float(s: str):\n    s = s.strip()\n    s = re.sub(r\"\\\\text\\{[^}]*\\}\", \"\", s)\n    s = re.sub(r\"\\\\,|\\\\;\", \"\", s)\n    s = s.replace(\",\", \"\").replace(\"%\", \"\")\n    frac = re.match(r\"\\\\frac\\{([^}]+)\\}\\{([^}]+)\\}\", s)\n    if frac:\n        try:\n            return float(frac.group(1)) / float(frac.group(2))\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n    try:\n        return float(s)\n    except Exception:\n        return None\n\n# ── Reward 1: FORMAT ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# <think> must open AND close. \\boxed{} must appear AFTER </think>.\ndef reward_format(completions, **kwargs) -> list:\n    scores = []\n    for comp in completions:\n        text  = _get_text(comp)\n        score = 0.0\n        if \"<think>\" in text and \"</think>\" in text:\n            score += 0.1\n            tail = text.split(\"</think>\")[-1]\n            if BOXED_PATTERN.search(tail):\n                score += 0.1\n        scores.append(score)\n    return scores\n\n\n# ── Reward 2: THINKING QUALITY ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Prevents <think>ok</think>\\boxed{42} gaming of format reward.\n# Requires ≥80 approximate tokens of real reasoning inside <think>.\ndef reward_thinking_quality(completions, **kwargs) -> list:\n    scores = []\n    for comp in completions:\n        text  = _get_text(comp)\n        score = 0.0\n        if \"<think>\" in text and \"</think>\" in text:\n            body          = text.split(\"<think>\")[-1].split(\"</think>\")[0].strip()\n            approx_tokens = len(body) / 4\n            if approx_tokens >= 80:\n                score = 0.5\n            elif approx_tokens >= 30:\n                score = 0.25\n        scores.append(score)\n    return scores\n\n\n# ── Reward 3: CORRECTNESS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Exact string / LaTeX match only — NO partial credit for answer appearing\n# anywhere in text. That pattern trained reward hacking (answer in <think>).\ndef reward_correctness(completions, answer, **kwargs) -> list:\n    scores = []\n    for comp, gt in zip(completions, answer):\n        text     = _get_text(comp)\n        gt_clean = extract_boxed(gt) if BOXED_PATTERN.search(gt) else gt.strip()\n        pred     = extract_boxed(text)\n        scores.append(4.0 if (pred and _norm(pred) == _norm(gt_clean)) else -1.0)\n    return scores\n\n\n# ── Reward 4: NUMERICAL EQUIVALENCE ──────────────────────────────────────────\n# Covers physics, unit conversion, algebra — any answer that parses as a float.\n# Handles fractions, LaTeX fractions, percentages, scientific notation.\n# 1% relative tolerance for full credit; 5% for partial.\ndef reward_numerical(completions, answer, **kwargs) -> list:\n    scores = []\n    for comp, gt in zip(completions, answer):\n        text     = _get_text(comp)\n        gt_clean = extract_boxed(gt) if BOXED_PATTERN.search(gt) else gt.strip()\n        pred     = extract_boxed(text)\n        if not pred:\n            scores.append(0.0)\n            continue\n        gt_val, pred_val = _try_float(gt_clean), _try_float(pred)\n        if gt_val is None or pred_val is None:\n            scores.append(0.0)\n            continue\n        if math.isclose(gt_val, pred_val, rel_tol=0.01, abs_tol=1e-6):\n            scores.append(3.0)\n        elif math.isclose(gt_val, pred_val, rel_tol=0.05, abs_tol=1e-4):\n            scores.append(1.0)\n        else:\n            scores.append(0.0)\n    return scores\n\n\n# ── Reward 5: ANTI-HACKING ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Detects and penalises the exploit: GT pasted inside <think> with wrong \\boxed{}.\n# Penalty -0.5 (hacking detected)\ndef reward_no_hacking(completions, answer, **kwargs) -> list:\n    scores = []\n    for comp, gt in zip(completions, answer):\n        text     = _get_text(comp)\n        gt_clean = extract_boxed(gt) if BOXED_PATTERN.search(gt) else gt.strip()\n        pred     = extract_boxed(text)\n        score    = 0.0\n        if \"<think>\" in text and \"</think>\" in text:\n            think_body   = text.split(\"<think>\")[-1].split(\"</think>\")[0]\n            gt_in_think  = _norm(gt_clean) in _norm(think_body)\n            pred_correct = _norm(pred) == _norm(gt_clean)\n            if gt_in_think and not pred_correct:\n                score = -0.5\n        scores.append(score)\n    return scores\n\n# ── REWARD 6: SOFT OVERLONG PUNISHMENT (Paper Eq. 13) ────────────────────\n# When response hits max_completion_length and is truncated,\n# it receives a soft penalty proportional to truncation severity.\n# Prevents reward noise from penalizing valid-but-long reasoning chains.\n# Lcache = buffer zone before hard truncation where penalty ramps up.\n\nMAX_COMPLETION_LENGTH = 768   # Must match dapo_config.max_completion_length\nLCACHE = 100                  # Penalty ramp-up window (last 100 tokens)\n\ndef reward_overlong_shaping(completions, **kwargs) -> list:\n    scores = []\n    for comp in completions:\n        text = _get_text(comp)\n        # Approximate token count (~4 chars per token)\n        approx_len = len(text) / 4\n\n        if approx_len <= (MAX_COMPLETION_LENGTH - LCACHE):\n            # Response fits cleanly — no penalty\n            scores.append(0.0)\n        elif approx_len <= MAX_COMPLETION_LENGTH:\n            # Inside the soft punishment zone — linear ramp\n            penalty = ((MAX_COMPLETION_LENGTH - LCACHE) - approx_len) / LCACHE\n            scores.append(penalty)   # Negative value\n        else:\n            # Hard truncation — maximum penalty\n            scores.append(-1.0)\n\n    return scores\n\nprint(\"[BAPO] 5-Reward system armed:\")\nprint(\"  reward_format           — max 0.2\")\nprint(\"  reward_thinking_quality — max 0.1\")\nprint(\"  reward_correctness      — max 4.0  (exact only, no hacking partial credit)\")\nprint(\"  reward_numerical        — max 3.0  (float equiv, 1% tol, frac/LaTeX aware)\")\nprint(\"  reward_no_hacking       — penalty -0.5 for answer-in-think exploit\")\nprint(\"  ─────────────────────────\")\nprint(\"  Combined ceiling        : 7.3 pts\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-11T19:41:47.487843Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-11T19:41:47.487942Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-11T19:41:47.496624Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-11T19:41:47.487931Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-11T19:41:47.496379Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"[BAPO] 5-Reward system armed:\n  reward_format           — max 0.2\n  reward_thinking_quality — max 0.1\n  reward_correctness      — max 4.0  (exact only, no hacking partial credit)\n  reward_numerical        — max 3.0  (float equiv, 1% tol, frac/LaTeX aware)\n  reward_no_hacking       — penalty -0.5 for answer-in-think exploit\n  ─────────────────────────\n  Combined ceiling        : 7.3 pts\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":18},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Step 3: VRAM Safety Check Before BAPO Training\n\ntraining is more VRAM-hungry than SFT because it holds **G=4 completions** in memory\nsimultaneously during the rollout phase. We check free VRAM before launching and\nabort with an actionable error if headroom is insufficient.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"gc.collect()\ntorch.cuda.empty_cache()\n\n# 1. Fetch the GPU Hardware Stats\ngpu_stats = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0)\nstart_gpu_memory = round(torch.cuda.max_memory_reserved() / 1024 / 1024 / 1024, 3)\nmax_memory = round(gpu_stats.total_memory / 1024 / 1024 / 1024, 3)\nfree_memory = max_memory - start_gpu_memory\n\nprint(f\"\\n GPU: {gpu_stats.name}\")\nprint(f\"   Total VRAM:    {max_memory} GB\")\nprint(f\"   Reserved VRAM: {start_gpu_memory} GB\")\nprint(f\"   Free VRAM:     {free_memory:.2f} GB\\n\")\n\nis_critical = free_memory < 4.0\nif is_critical:\n    print(\" WARNING: Less than 4GB free VRAM. Training may OOM.\")\n    print(\"   Consider reducing MAX_SEQ_LEN or LoRA rank.\")\n\n# ==========================================\n# 2. SEABORN VRAM HUD GRAPH\n# ==========================================\nsns.set_theme(style=\"dark\", rc={\n    \"axes.facecolor\": \"#121212\", \n    \"figure.facecolor\": \"#121212\",\n    \"text.color\": \"white\"\n})\n\n# Create a DataFrame for Seaborn to digest\ndf = pd.DataFrame({\n    'Component': ['VRAM'],\n    'Used': [start_gpu_memory],\n    'Total': [max_memory]\n})\n\nf, ax = plot.subplots(figsize=(8, 1.2))\n\n# Plot the background bar (Total VRAM / Free Space) in dark gray\nsns.barplot(x=\"Total\", y=\"Component\", data=df, color=\"#2a2a2a\", ax=ax)\n\n# Plot the foreground bar (Used VRAM) overriding the color based on danger levels\ncolor_reserved = '#ff3333' if is_critical else '#00e5ff' # Red if critical, Cyan if safe\nsns.barplot(x=\"Used\", y=\"Component\", data=df, color=color_reserved, ax=ax)\n\n# Clean up the axes for the pure HUD look\nax.set(ylabel=\"\", xlabel=\"\")\nax.set_xticks([])\nax.set_yticks([])\nsns.despine(left=True, bottom=True)\n\n# Add dynamic text overlays right inside the bars\nif start_gpu_memory > 2.0:\n    plot.text(start_gpu_memory / 2, 0, f\"USED: {start_gpu_memory:.1f} GB\", \n             color='#121212', va='center', ha='center', fontweight='bold', fontsize=10)\n    \nif free_memory > 2.0:\n    plot.text(start_gpu_memory + (free_memory / 2), 0, f\"FREE: {free_memory:.1f} GB\", \n             color='#888888', va='center', ha='center', fontweight='bold', fontsize=10)\n\n# THE FIX: Removed letterspacing, manually spaced the title for the cinematic look\nplot.title(\"S Y S T E M   M E M O R Y   S T A T U S\", color='white', fontsize=11, pad=10, fontweight='bold')\nplot.tight_layout()\nplot.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-11T19:41:47.496987Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-11T19:41:47.497073Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-11T19:41:48.279633Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-11T19:41:47.497064Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-11T19:41:48.279363Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"\n GPU: NVIDIA RTX PRO 6000 Blackwell Server Edition\n   Total VRAM:    94.971 GB\n   Reserved VRAM: 94.316 GB\n   Free VRAM:     0.66 GB\n\n WARNING: Less than 4GB free VRAM. Training may OOM.\n   Consider reducing MAX_SEQ_LEN or LoRA rank.\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 800x120 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":19},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Step 4: Configure The Custom BAPO Trainer\n\nHere we subclass the Hugging Face `BAPOTrainer` to intercept the loss calculation. We inject the Asymmetric Clip-Higher logic and the Dynamic Sampling filter to brutally optimize our Kaggle compute window.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\nfrom trl.trainer.base_config import _BaseConfig\n\n@dataclass\nclass BAPOConfig(_BaseConfig):\n    # Core Training & Generation\n    learning_rate: float = field(default=1e-6)\n    num_generations: int = field(default=4)\n    max_completion_length: int = field(default=512)\n    temperature: float = field(default=0.9)\n    top_p: float = field(default=0.95)\n    generation_batch_size: Optional[int] = field(default=None)\n    steps_per_generation: Optional[int] = field(default=None)\n    \n    # BAPO Specific Adaptive Bounds\n    ratio_lower_start: float = field(default=0.8)\n    ratio_lower_max: float = field(default=1.0)\n    ratio_lower_step: float = field(default=0.05)\n    ratio_upper_start: float = field(default=1.2)\n    ratio_upper_max: float = field(default=1.5)\n    ratio_upper_step: float = field(default=0.05)\n    adv_ratio_target: float = field(default=1.0)\n    bapo_eps: float = field(default=1e-8)\n    \n    # Reward\n    reward_weights: Optional[list[float]] = field(default=None)\n\n    def __post_init__(self):\n        super().__post_init__()\n        num_processes = self.world_size\n        \n        if self.generation_batch_size is None and self.steps_per_generation is None:\n            self.steps_per_generation = self.gradient_accumulation_steps\n            self.generation_batch_size = self.per_device_train_batch_size * num_processes * self.steps_per_generation\n        elif self.generation_batch_size is not None and self.steps_per_generation is None:\n            self.steps_per_generation = self.generation_batch_size // (self.per_device_train_batch_size * num_processes)\n        elif self.generation_batch_size is None and self.steps_per_generation is not None:\n            self.generation_batch_size = self.per_device_train_batch_size * num_processes * self.steps_per_generation\n            \n        if self.num_generations < 2:\n            raise ValueError(\"BAPO requires at least 2 generations per prompt to calculate advantages.\")\n\nimport time\nimport torch\nimport torch.nn.functional as F\nfrom collections import defaultdict\nfrom transformers import PreTrainedModel, PreTrainedTokenizerBase, GenerationConfig\nfrom trl.trainer.base_trainer import _BaseTrainer\nfrom trl.trainer.utils import RepeatSampler, pad, selective_log_softmax\nfrom accelerate.utils import gather\nimport sys\nimport gc\n\nclass BAPOTrainer(_BaseTrainer):\n    def __init__(self, model, reward_funcs, args, train_dataset, processing_class,callbacks=None):\n        self.reward_funcs = reward_funcs if isinstance(reward_funcs, list) else [reward_funcs]\n        self.reward_weights = torch.ones(len(self.reward_funcs), dtype=torch.float32) if args.reward_weights is None else torch.tensor(args.reward_weights, dtype=torch.float32)\n        \n        self.max_completion_length = args.max_completion_length\n        self.num_generations = args.num_generations\n        self.temperature = args.temperature\n        self.top_p = args.top_p\n        \n        # BAPO bounds\n        self.ratio_lower_start = args.ratio_lower_start\n        self.ratio_lower_max = args.ratio_lower_max\n        self.ratio_lower_step = args.ratio_lower_step\n        self.ratio_upper_start = args.ratio_upper_start\n        self.ratio_upper_max = args.ratio_upper_max\n        self.ratio_upper_step = args.ratio_upper_step\n        self.adv_ratio_target = args.adv_ratio_target\n        self.bapo_eps = args.bapo_eps\n        \n        self._step = 0\n        self._buffered_inputs = None\n        self._metrics = {\"train\": defaultdict(list)}\n        self._stats = {\"last_logged_step\": -1}\n        self.shuffle_dataset = True\n\n        self._nemotron_cache_cls = None\n        for _mod_name, _mod in list(sys.modules.items()):\n            if 'nemotron' in _mod_name.lower():\n                _cc = getattr(_mod, 'NemotronHHybridDynamicCache', None)\n                if _cc is not None:\n                    self._nemotron_cache_cls = _cc\n                    print(f\"[BAPO] Found Nemotron Cache in {_mod_name}. Fast generation locked in.\")\n                    break\n\n        super().__init__(\n            model=model,\n            args=args,\n            data_collator=lambda x: x,\n            train_dataset=train_dataset,\n            processing_class=processing_class,\n            callbacks=callbacks,\n            compute_loss_func=\"disable\", \n        )\n        self.model_accepts_loss_kwargs = False\n        \n        self.generation_config = GenerationConfig(\n            max_new_tokens=self.max_completion_length,\n            min_new_tokens=256, \n            do_sample=True,\n            pad_token_id=self.processing_class.pad_token_id,\n            eos_token_id=self.processing_class.eos_token_id,\n            temperature=self.temperature,\n            top_p=self.top_p,\n            disable_compile=True\n        )\n\n    def get_train_dataloader(self):\n        return self._get_dataloader(\n            dataset=self.train_dataset,\n            description=\"Training\",\n            batch_size=self._train_batch_size * self.args.steps_per_generation,\n            sampler_fn=self._get_train_sampler,\n            is_training=True,\n        )\n\n    def _get_train_sampler(self, dataset=None):\n        return RepeatSampler(\n            data_source=dataset or self.train_dataset,\n            mini_repeat_count=self.num_generations,\n            batch_size=self.args.generation_batch_size // self.num_generations,\n            repeat_count=self.args.steps_per_generation,\n            shuffle=self.shuffle_dataset,\n            seed=self.args.seed,\n        )\n\n    def _generate_completions(self, prompts):\n        device = self.accelerator.device\n        prompt_ids = self.processing_class(text=prompts)[\"input_ids\"]\n        prompt_tensors = [torch.tensor(ids) for ids in prompt_ids]\n        padded_ids = pad(prompt_tensors, padding_value=self.processing_class.pad_token_id, padding_side=\"left\")\n        attention_mask = pad([torch.ones_like(t) for t in prompt_tensors], padding_value=0, padding_side=\"left\")\n        \n        generate_inputs = {\"input_ids\": padded_ids.to(device), \"attention_mask\": attention_mask.to(device)}\n        \n# ── 1. The Elegant Context Switch ──\n        self.model.eval() \n        self.model.config.use_cache = True\n        \n        # 🚨 THE NEMOTRON HYBRID CACHE INJECTION 🚨\n        if getattr(self, \"_nemotron_cache_cls\", None) is not None:\n            try:\n                # Try instantiating without arguments\n                generate_inputs[\"past_key_values\"] = self._nemotron_cache_cls()\n            except TypeError:\n                # Some versions require the config object to be passed\n                generate_inputs[\"past_key_values\"] = self._nemotron_cache_cls(self.model.config)\n\n        # ── 2. Sprint Generation ──\n        with torch.no_grad():\n            prompt_completion_ids = self.model.generate(\n                **generate_inputs, \n                generation_config=self.generation_config\n            )\n            \n        # ── 3. Securely Restore Training State ──\n        self.model.train()\n        self.model.config.use_cache = False\n        \n        # Extract completions\n        prompt_length = generate_inputs[\"input_ids\"].size(1)\n        completion_ids = prompt_completion_ids[:, prompt_length:]\n        \n        is_eos = completion_ids == self.processing_class.eos_token_id\n        eos_idx = torch.full((is_eos.size(0),), is_eos.size(1), dtype=torch.long, device=device)\n        eos_idx[is_eos.any(dim=1)] = is_eos.int().argmax(dim=1)[is_eos.any(dim=1)]\n        sequence_indices = torch.arange(is_eos.size(1), device=device).expand(is_eos.size(0), -1)\n        completion_mask = (sequence_indices <= eos_idx.unsqueeze(1)).int()\n        \n        completion_ids_list = [c[m].tolist() for c, m in zip(completion_ids.cpu(), completion_mask.bool().cpu())]\n        completions = self.processing_class.batch_decode(completion_ids_list, skip_special_tokens=True)\n        \n        return prompt_ids, completion_ids_list, completions\n\n    def _calculate_rewards(self, prompts, completions, completion_ids_list, answers):\n        device = self.accelerator.device\n        rewards_per_func = torch.zeros(len(prompts), len(self.reward_funcs), device=device)\n        \n        for i, reward_func in enumerate(self.reward_funcs):\n            output = reward_func(prompts=prompts, completions=completions, completion_ids=completion_ids_list, answer=answers)\n            output = [r if r is not None else torch.nan for r in output]\n            rewards_per_func[:, i] = torch.tensor(output, dtype=torch.float32, device=device)\n\n        rewards_per_func = gather(rewards_per_func)\n        rewards = (rewards_per_func * self.reward_weights.to(device).unsqueeze(0)).nansum(dim=1)\n        \n        mean_grouped_rewards = rewards.view(-1, self.num_generations).mean(dim=1).repeat_interleave(self.num_generations)\n        std_grouped_rewards = rewards.view(-1, self.num_generations).std(dim=1).repeat_interleave(self.num_generations)\n        \n        advantages = (rewards - mean_grouped_rewards) / (std_grouped_rewards + 1e-4)\n\n        group_max = rewards.view(-1, self.num_generations).max(dim=1)[0].repeat_interleave(self.num_generations)\n        advantages = torch.where(group_max == 0.0, torch.tensor(-1.0, device=device), advantages)\n        \n        # 🎙️ 2. THE DIAGNOSTIC WIRETAP\n        if self._step % 5 == 0 and self.accelerator.process_index == 0:\n            print(f\"\\n[WIRETAP | STEP {self._step}]\")\n            print(f\"COMPLETION 1: {repr(completions[0][:150])}\")\n            print(f\"GROUP REWARDS: {rewards[:self.num_generations].tolist()}\")\n            print(f\"GROUP ADVANTAGES: {advantages[:self.num_generations].tolist()}\\n\")\n\n        process_slice = slice(self.accelerator.process_index * len(prompts), (self.accelerator.process_index + 1) * len(prompts))\n        return advantages[process_slice]\n\n    def _prepare_inputs(self, generation_batch):\n        if self._step % self.args.steps_per_generation == 0 or self._buffered_inputs is None:\n            prompts  = [item[\"prompt\"]  for item in generation_batch]\n            answers  = [item[\"answer\"]  for item in generation_batch]  \n            prompt_ids, completion_ids, completions = self._generate_completions(prompts)\n            advantages = self._calculate_rewards(prompts, completions, completion_ids, answers)  \n            \n            device = self.accelerator.device\n            prompt_ids_tensor = pad([torch.tensor(ids) for ids in prompt_ids], padding_value=self.processing_class.pad_token_id, padding_side=\"left\").to(device)\n            completion_ids_tensor = pad([torch.tensor(ids) for ids in completion_ids], padding_value=self.processing_class.pad_token_id, padding_side=\"right\").to(device)\n            \n            prompt_mask = (prompt_ids_tensor != self.processing_class.pad_token_id).long()\n            \n            lengths = torch.tensor([max(1, len(ids)) for ids in completion_ids], device=device)\n            seq_len = max(1, completion_ids_tensor.shape[1])\n            indices = torch.arange(seq_len, device=device).expand(len(lengths), -1)\n            completion_mask = (indices < lengths.unsqueeze(1)).long()\n\n            # Compute old logps\n            _full_ids  = torch.cat([prompt_ids_tensor, completion_ids_tensor], dim=1)\n            _full_mask = torch.cat([prompt_mask, completion_mask], dim=1)\n            with torch.no_grad():\n                _old_logits = self.model(\n                    input_ids=_full_ids, attention_mask=_full_mask\n                ).logits[:, :-1, :]\n                _old_logps = selective_log_softmax(\n                    _old_logits.float(), _full_ids[:, 1:]\n                )\n                old_per_token_logps = _old_logps[:, -completion_ids_tensor.shape[1]:]\n\n            batch_dict = {\n                \"prompt_ids\"          : prompt_ids_tensor,\n                \"prompt_mask\"         : prompt_mask,\n                \"completion_ids\"      : completion_ids_tensor,\n                \"completion_mask\"     : completion_mask,\n                \"advantages\"          : advantages,\n                \"old_per_token_logps\" : old_per_token_logps,   \n            }\n            \n            chunk_size = len(prompts) // self.args.steps_per_generation\n            self._buffered_inputs = [{k: v[i:i+chunk_size] for k, v in batch_dict.items()} for i in range(0, len(prompts), chunk_size)]\n            \n        return self._buffered_inputs[self._step % self.args.steps_per_generation]\n\n    def compute_loss(self, model, inputs, return_outputs=False, num_items_in_batch=None):\n        input_ids = torch.cat([inputs[\"prompt_ids\"], inputs[\"completion_ids\"]], dim=1)\n        attention_mask = torch.cat([inputs[\"prompt_mask\"], inputs[\"completion_mask\"]], dim=1)\n        completion_mask = inputs[\"completion_mask\"]\n        advantages = inputs[\"advantages\"].unsqueeze(1)\n        \n        logits = model(input_ids=input_ids, attention_mask=attention_mask).logits[:, :-1, :]\n        labels = input_ids[:, 1:]\n        \n        log_probs = selective_log_softmax(logits.float(), labels)\n        new_logps = log_probs[:, -completion_mask.shape[1]:]\n        \n        old_logps = inputs.get(\"old_per_token_logps\", new_logps.detach())\n        ratio = torch.exp(new_logps - old_logps)\n        clip_low, clip_high = self.ratio_lower_start, self.ratio_upper_start\n\n        def get_pos_neg_ratio(c_low, c_high):\n            r_pos = torch.minimum(ratio, torch.tensor(c_high, device=ratio.device))\n            r_neg = torch.maximum(ratio, torch.tensor(c_low, device=ratio.device))\n            eff_adv = torch.where(advantages >= 0, r_pos, r_neg) * advantages * completion_mask\n            \n            pos_c = eff_adv.clamp(min=0).sum()\n            neg_c = (-eff_adv.clamp(max=0)).sum()\n            return float(\"inf\") if neg_c <= 0 else (pos_c / (neg_c + self.bapo_eps)).item()\n\n        current_ratio = get_pos_neg_ratio(clip_low, clip_high)\n\n        while current_ratio < self.adv_ratio_target and clip_low < self.ratio_lower_max and self.ratio_lower_step > 0:\n            clip_low = min(clip_low + self.ratio_lower_step, self.ratio_lower_max)\n            current_ratio = get_pos_neg_ratio(clip_low, clip_high)\n\n        while current_ratio < self.adv_ratio_target and clip_high < self.ratio_upper_max and self.ratio_upper_step > 0:\n            clip_high = min(clip_high + self.ratio_upper_step, self.ratio_upper_max)\n            current_ratio = get_pos_neg_ratio(clip_low, clip_high)\n\n        # ── Official BAPO loss with extreme negative clamp ────────────────\n        clipped_ratio   = torch.clamp(ratio, clip_low, clip_high)\n        pg_losses1      = -advantages * ratio\n        pg_losses2      = -advantages * clipped_ratio\n        clip_pg_losses1 = torch.maximum(pg_losses1, pg_losses2)\n\n        clip_ratio_c    = 3.0\n        pg_losses3      = -advantages * clip_ratio_c\n        clip_pg_losses2 = torch.minimum(pg_losses3, clip_pg_losses1)\n\n        per_token_loss  = torch.where(\n            advantages < 0, clip_pg_losses2, clip_pg_losses1\n        ) * completion_mask\n\n        loss = per_token_loss.sum() / completion_mask.sum().clamp(min=1.0)\n        \n        if self._step > 0 and self._step % 5 == 0 and self._step != self._stats[\"last_logged_step\"]:\n            self._stats[\"last_logged_step\"] = self._step\n            print(f\"[BAPO NATIVE] Step={self._step} | Bounds=[{clip_low:.2f}, {clip_high:.2f}] | Ratio={current_ratio:.2f} | loss={loss.item():.4f}\")\n\n        self._step += 1\n        return (loss, None) if return_outputs else loss\n\nimport torch\nimport torch.nn.functional as F\nimport gc, os, sys, time\nfrom transformers import TrainerCallback\n\n# ── HARDWARE FLAGS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ntorch.backends.cuda.matmul.allow_tf32 = True\ntorch.backends.cudnn.allow_tf32       = True\nos.environ[\"PYTORCH_CUDA_ALLOC_CONF\"] = \"expandable_segments:True\"\n\ngc.collect()\ntorch.cuda.empty_cache()\nprint(f\"[BAPO] VRAM before training: {torch.cuda.memory_reserved()/1024**3:.2f} GB reserved\")\n\n# ── FIND NEMOTRONH CACHE CLASS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# NemotronH is a hybrid Attention+Mamba model.\n# Without NemotronHHybridDynamicCache, generate() does full O(L²) recompute\n# on every token — 3-4x slower than cached O(L) generation.\n_NEMOTRON_CACHE_CLS = None\nfor _mod_name, _mod in list(sys.modules.items()):\n    if 'nemotron' in _mod_name.lower():\n        _cc = getattr(_mod, 'NemotronHHybridDynamicCache', None)\n        if _cc is not None:\n            _NEMOTRON_CACHE_CLS = _cc\n            print(f\"[BAPO] NemotronHHybridDynamicCache found in {_mod_name} — fast generation enabled.\")\n            break\nif _NEMOTRON_CACHE_CLS is None:\n    print(\"[BAPO] WARNING: NemotronHHybridDynamicCache not found. Generation will be slow (O(L²)).\")\n\n\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nclass KaggleTimeLimitCallback(TrainerCallback):\n    \"\"\"Measures from TRAINING STEP 1 — not notebook start.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, max_hours=10.0):\n        self.max_seconds         = max_hours * 3600\n        self.training_start_time = None\n\n    def on_step_begin(self, args, state, control, **kwargs):\n        if self.training_start_time is None:\n            self.training_start_time = time.time()\n            print(f\"[TIMER] Training clock started. Budget: {self.max_seconds/3600:.1f}h\")\n\n    def on_step_end(self, args, state, control, **kwargs):\n        if self.training_start_time is None:\n            return\n        elapsed = time.time() - self.training_start_time\n        if elapsed >= self.max_seconds:\n            print(f\"\\n[SAFETY] {elapsed/3600:.2f}h elapsed. Stopping and saving.\")\n            control.should_training_stop = True\n\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONFIG FACTORY — per-run config with category-specific hyperparams\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nREWARD_FUNCS = [\n    reward_format,\n    reward_thinking_quality,\n    reward_correctness,\n    reward_numerical,\n    reward_no_hacking,\n    reward_overlong_shaping,\n]\n\ndef build_bapo_config(run_cfg: dict) -> BAPOConfig:\n    \"\"\"Build a BAPOConfig for one sequential BAPO run.\"\"\"\n    return BAPOConfig(\n        output_dir                  = f\"/kaggle/working/bapo_{run_cfg['name']}\",\n        # max_completion_length       = 768,\n        num_generations             = 4,\n        temperature                 = 0.9,\n        top_p                       = 0.95,\n        per_device_train_batch_size = 1,\n        gradient_accumulation_steps = 4,\n        gradient_checkpointing      = False,\n        optim                       = \"paged_adamw_8bit\",\n        learning_rate               = run_cfg[\"lr\"],\n        max_steps                   = run_cfg[\"max_steps\"],\n        warmup_ratio                = 0.05,\n        lr_scheduler_type           = \"cosine\",\n        weight_decay                = 0.01,\n        max_grad_norm               = 1.0,\n        bf16                        = True,\n        fp16                        = False,\n        dataloader_pin_memory       = True,\n        dataloader_num_workers      = 2,\n        logging_steps               = 5,\n        save_strategy               = \"steps\",\n        save_steps                  = 25,\n        report_to                   = \"none\",\n        seed                        = 3407,\n        remove_unused_columns       = False,\n    )\n\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SEQUENTIAL BAPO TRAINING LOOP\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nTOTAL_BUDGET_HOURS = 10.0\n_global_start = time.time()\n\nprint(f\"\\n[BAPO] COMMENCING SEQUENTIAL TRAINING — {len(BAPO_RUNS)} runs\")\nprint(f\"[BAPO] Total budget: {TOTAL_BUDGET_HOURS}h\\n\")\n\nfor run_idx, run_cfg in enumerate(BAPO_RUNS):\n    elapsed_h = (time.time() - _global_start) / 3600\n    remaining_h = TOTAL_BUDGET_HOURS - elapsed_h\n    if remaining_h < 0.5:\n        print(f\"\\n[SAFETY] Only {remaining_h:.2f}h left. Skipping run '{run_cfg['name']}'.\")\n        break\n\n    ds = bapo_run_datasets[run_cfg[\"name\"]]\n    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n    print(f\"[BAPO RUN {run_idx+1}/{len(BAPO_RUNS)}] '{run_cfg['name']}'\")\n    print(f\"  {run_cfg['description']}\")\n    print(f\"  Samples: {len(ds)} | LR: {run_cfg['lr']:.0e} | Steps: {run_cfg['max_steps']}\")\n    print(f\"  Time elapsed: {elapsed_h:.2f}h | Remaining: {remaining_h:.2f}h\")\n    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n\n    cfg = build_bapo_config(run_cfg)\n    run_hours = min(remaining_h - 0.3, TOTAL_BUDGET_HOURS / len(BAPO_RUNS))\n\n    trainer = BAPOTrainer(\n        model            = model,\n        args             = cfg,\n        train_dataset    = ds,\n        reward_funcs     = REWARD_FUNCS,\n        processing_class = tokenizer,\n        callbacks        = [KaggleTimeLimitCallback(max_hours=run_hours)],\n    )\n\n    trainer.train()\n\n    # Save after each run\n    save_path = f\"/kaggle/working/bapo_{run_cfg['name']}_final\"\n    model.save_pretrained(save_path)\n    print(f\"[BAPO] Run '{run_cfg['name']}' complete. Adapter saved to {save_path}\")\n\n    # Clean up trainer to free VRAM\n    del trainer\n    gc.collect()\n    torch.cuda.empty_cache()\n\n# Save the final combined adapter\n_final_path = \"/kaggle/working/nemotron_bapo_adapter_final\"\nmodel.save_pretrained(_final_path)\ntokenizer.save_pretrained(_final_path)\n\ntotal_elapsed = (time.time() - _global_start) / 3600\nprint(f\"\\n[BAPO] ALL RUNS COMPLETE in {total_elapsed:.2f}h\")\nprint(f\"[BAPO] Final adapter: {_final_path}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-11T20:26:45.842114Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-11T20:26:45.842253Z","execution_failed":"2026-05-11T20:37:06.712Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"